<DocsLayout title="Requirements" description="Meet the client, understand the brief, and write the PRD with data classification and SLA targets.">
  <h1 class="mb-6">Requirements</h1>
  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-4">You know the process. Client brief, prompt plus template, review. The new wrinkles: a data classification table (what's PII, what's medical information), an SLA section (uptime targets and maintenance windows), and a permissions matrix with location-based scoping.</p>

  <Callout variant="info">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>New tool: Linear.</strong> This project uses Linear instead of GitHub Projects for project management. Same kanban concepts — backlog, in progress, done. Different interface. We switch to show that the skill transfers across tools. If you can manage a project in GitHub Projects, you can manage it in Linear. The underlying workflow is the same.</p>
  </Callout>

  <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">Work through these in order:</p>

